          </ul>
        </div>

        <h2 class="article__subheader">Member Experience</h2>

        <p>We had two driving forces when redesigning the member experience: simplicity and celebration. We simplified the goal setting experience to two things: one long-term goal and one short-term goal ‚Äì both in the member's own words. This greatly simplifies the experience, for members now keep track of one goal at a time (instead of potentially nine things at once).</p>

        <p>In addition to the member-entered goals, we can also surface general program expectations (e.g. come to group four times this week) and personalized interventions, which we didn't do before. This is important for keeping members and staff on the same page, and being more transparent about what we expect from members to remain engaged in our program.</p>

