        <p>In terms of actions, counselors have the same abilities a member has ‚Äì and more. Counselors can add, edit, remove, and replace a member's goals, as well as mark them as complete. The ability for staff to act on a member's behalf ‚Äì if needed ‚Äì closes the gap between member and staff, and creates a seamless, frictionless experience for the member. Staff can also see alerts and badges that call out things like stale or overdue goals, to help them prioritize what actions to take next.</p>


